description:
Subjects Addressed:
(1) Mark Finley urges SDA members to accept whatever the final vote is on women's ordination and get along with the "mission of the church
(2) The apostate new organization also has "the mission" of the church at the core (1SM 204)
(3) Jewish leaders persuaded the people to choose Barabbas and crucify Jesus, while declaring their only king to be Caesar
(4) The choice between Christ and Barabbas represents the Mark of the Beast Crisis--Sabbath versus Sunday, the commandments of God versus the commandments of men
(5) The leaders of God's chosen denomination, the Seventh-day Adventist Church, will persuade men to go against God's laws and accept the laws of men
(6) The Mark of the Beast Crisis is right upon us as indicated by the prevalence of licentiousness
(7) U.S. President Barack Obama now believes the U.S. Constitution guarantees the right to same same-sex marriage in all 50 states. 
(8) To combat the legalized widespread immorality, individuals will cry out for change, the constitution will be altered and utterly repudiated, which will give rise to the enforcement of the Sunday Law
(9) Individuals are already preparing to go along with their leaders and the majority, because prior to this time, they have been yielding step-by-step
(10) God is calling upon His people to have the true spirit of Protestantism--putting the Word of God above the civil magistrate and above the visible church, teaching and experiencing salvation through faith in Christ alone, and the sole infallibility of the scriptures
(11) Many have the erroneous notion that the mere connection and membership in any denomination, including the Seventh-Day Adventist Denomination, guarantees their salvation, just like to Jews of old thought
(12) We must convert, with Christ's help, from merely being seeds of Abraham (children born of flesh) to becoming children of Abraham

Website: www.prophesyagain.org
